parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheels lock up without warning
the vehicle skids to a stop
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the transfer case during the recall can lead to the failure of the transfer case, causing accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transfer case is not replaced during the recall
only the fluid is filled up
the dealership denies responsibility for the failure
the dealership blames the owner for the failure.

symptoms: excessive breaking of the timing belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misrouting of the rear brake line can cause it to rub against the rim, leading to damage and potentially affecting brake performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake line is pointed towards the rim
the brake line rubs against the rim
damage to the rim or brake line is observed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seizure and hanging of the rear brakes can cause a loss of braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The rear brakes seize and hang
the vehicle takes longer to stop.
